The paper discusses sparse signal modeling, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. The use of learned overcomplete dictionaries and the application of sparse modeling in signal processing and machine learning suggest that the paper could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The focus on image denoising and classification problems indicates that the paper could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The use of the minimum description length (MDL) principle suggests that the paper could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory). The mention of low-rank matrix recovery in video applications suggests that the paper could belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) or cs.MM (Multimedia). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.CV, and cs.IT, followed by cs.NA and cs.MM.
